            "doi": "10.1186/s12859-014-0394-y",
            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "\u00a9 Grimonprez et al.; licensee BioMed Central Ltd.Background: Last generations of Single Nucleotide Polymorphism (SNP) arrays allow to study copy-number variations in addition to genotyping measures. Results:, standing for multi-patient analysis (MPA) of genomic markers, is an R-package devoted to: (i) efficient segmentation and (ii) selection of genomic markers from multi-patient copy number and SNP data profiles. It provides wrappers from commonly used packages to streamline their repeated (sometimes difficult) manipulation, offering an easy-to-use pipeline for beginners in R. Conclusions: provides an easy tool to analyze data from SNP arrays in R. The R-package is available on CRAN.",
                "authors": [
